expectedResults.title: Reflected XSS via Case-Insensitive Script Tag Filter
expectedResults.reason: The expected XSS vulnerability in the xss7 endpoint was not discovered by the penetration test. The actual findings focus on infrastructure and configuration vulnerabilities (path traversal, cache bypass, server headers, missing security headers) but do not include any reflected XSS findings.

actualResults.title: Path Traversal in Static File Serving via ../ Directory Sequences
actualResults.location: Static file serving endpoint at http://localhost:5001/static/
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - This is a legitimate vulnerability not covered by the expected findings.

actualResults.title: Cache Key Bypass via Path Parameters (CVE-2019-14806)
actualResults.location: Static file handler cache mechanism for /static/ endpoints
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - This is a known CVE affecting Werkzeug 1.0.1.

actualResults.title: Sensitive Server Information Disclosure via Server Header
actualResults.location: HTTP Server response header on all endpoints
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - The application exposes version information in Server headers.

actualResults.title: Missing Security Headers
actualResults.location: HTTP response headers across all endpoints
actualResults.assessment: New discovery - The application fails to implement critical security headers.
